        "text": "**Sedentary crop farming**: Sedentary crop farmers live in permanent settlements and crop production is their main source of livelihood, although this is usually supplemented by income from raising domestic animals. It has been estimated that lowland dry farming systems which are crop production oriented, occupies 10% of the world’s dry lands, supporting 10 times the number of people that are pastoralists. In such environment, incidence of unreliable rainfall creates an acute food shortage and unless livestock is few and closely integrated with crop  production, there is the probability of over grazing  which compounds the problem of environmental degradation (UNRISD, 1997)."
